net.rptools.maptool.model.MacroButtonPro.toolTip:
Given a string like:
"4d6 + 2 + 2d8 - 6 - 2d20"
return an object:
[
        {
            "diceRolled": 4,
            "diceSize": 6
        },
        {
            "diceRolled": 2,
            "diceSize": 8,
        },
        {
            "diceRolled": 2,
            "diceSize": 20,
            "subtract": 1
        },
        {
        		"diceRolled": 0,
        		"diceSize": 0,
        	  "bonus": -4
        }
]
Keys:
	"diceRolled": The number of dice rolled; always positive.
	"diceSize": The size of the die; always positive.
	"bonus": The amount added to the roll; may be positive or negative.
	"subtract": boolean value (0, 1) where false means the roll is subtracted and positive means the roll is added. When subtract is unspecified, addition is assumed.

"Why are the bonus values all added up and by itself?"
"...Shuttup."
